:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">131</span></span></a> - Quickly run npm scripts by prefix without typing the full name.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/RyanZim/edit-script\">edit-script</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/RyanZim/edit-script\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">9</span></span></a> - Edit npm scripts from the command line without worrying about JSON escaping.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ruyadorno/ntl\">ntl</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ruyadorno/ntl\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">872</span></span></a> - Interactive cli menu to list and run npm scripts.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"cross-platform-shell-reference\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#cross-platform-shell-reference\" aria-label=\"cross platform shell reference permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cross-platform Shell Reference</h2>\n<p>A quick reference of the shell operators &#x26; commands that work the same on Unix and Windows.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use <code class=\"language-text\">&amp;&amp;</code> to run commands in sequence. If a command fails, the script exits.</li>\n<li>Use <code class=\"language-text\">|</code> to pipe the stdout of one command into the stdin of the next. (<code class=\"language-text\">do-something | something else</code>)</li>\n<li>Use <code class=\"language-text\">&gt;</code> to write the stdout of a command to a file. (<code class=\"language-text\">do-something &gt; file</code>)</li>\n<li>Use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;</code> to send the contents of a file to a command's stdin. (<code class=\"language-text\">command &lt; file</code>)</li>\n<li>Use <code class=\"language-text\">cd &lt;dir&gt;</code> to change the current working directory to <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;dir&gt;</code>. Note that <code class=\"language-text\">cd</code> alone prints the current working directory on windows, but changes the working directory to <code class=\"language-text\">~</code> on *nix.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"npm-run-reference\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#npm-run-reference\" aria-label=\"npm run reference permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code> Reference</h2>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">npm run-script</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code>; they both do the same thing, but <code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code> is shorter.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Run just <code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code> to print a list of scripts.</li>\n<li>Running <code class=\"language-text\">npm run script</code> (where <code class=\"language-text\">script</code> is the name of your script) will run <code class=\"language-text\">prescript</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">script</code>, and <code class=\"language-text\">postscript</code>; in that order.\n<ul>\n<li>You can't nest <code class=\"language-text\">pre</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">post</code> hooks (i.e. <code class=\"language-text\">preprescript</code> won't work).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>You can pass arguments to your scripts by passing <code class=\"language-text\">--</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code>, followed by the arguments. Example: Given the script <code class=\"language-text\">&quot;mocha&quot;: &quot;mocha&quot;</code>, you can run <code class=\"language-text\">npm run mocha -- --reporter xunit</code>. This effectively runs <code class=\"language-text\">mocha --reporter xunit</code>.</li>\n<li>Running <code class=\"language-text\">npm test</code> is the same as running <code class=\"language-text\">npm run test</code>. The same applies to <code class=\"language-text\">npm start</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">npm stop</code>.</li>\n<li>You can run <code class=\"language-text\">npm run &lt;script&gt; -s</code> to silence the default npm output (useful for calling a script within another script).</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"contributing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contributing\" aria-label=\"contributing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contributing</h2>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>.</p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#awesome-npm-scripts-awesome\">Awesome npm Scripts <img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#contents\">Contents</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#articles\">Articles</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#videostalks\">Videos/Talks</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#task-runners\">Task Runners</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#file-watchers\">File Watchers</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#dev-servers\">Dev Servers</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#cross-platform-utilities\">Cross-platform Utilities</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#utility-packs\">Utility Packs</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#other-utilities\">Other Utilities</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#miscellaneous\">Miscellaneous</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#cross-platform-shell-reference\">Cross-platform Shell Reference</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#npm-run-reference\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code> Reference</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#contributing\">Contributing</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"awesome-npm-scripts-awesome","value":"Awesome npm Scripts Awesome","depth":1},{"id":"contents","value":"Contents","depth":2},{"id":"articles","value":"Articles","depth":2},{"id":"videostalks","value":"Videos/Talks","depth":2},{"id":"task-runners","value":"Task Runners","depth":2},{"id":"file-watchers","value":"File Watchers","depth":2},{"id":"dev-servers","value":"Dev Servers","depth":2},{"id":"cross-platform-utilities","value":"Cross-platform Utilities","depth":2},{"id":"utility-packs","value":"Utility Packs","depth":3},{"id":"other-utilities","value":"Other Utilities","depth":2},{"id":"miscellaneous","value":"Miscellaneous","depth":2},{"id":"cross-platform-shell-reference","value":"Cross-platform Shell Reference","depth":2},{"id":"npm-run-reference","value":"<code class=\"language-text\">npm run</code> Reference","depth":2},{"id":"contributing","value":"Contributing","depth":2}]},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2022-10-14T06:39:30.142Z","repo":"RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","description":"Everything awesome related to npm scripts and using npm as a build tool.","readmeItemsUpdatedTime":1663959728000,"descriptionHTML":"<div>Everything awesome related to npm scripts and using npm as a build tool.</div>","stargazerCount":673,"category":"Programming Languages"},"previous":{"id":"6517901e-70a1-59f6-aaee-ef1d70da31c7","fields":{"repo":"sindresorhus/awesome-observables","slug":"/sindresorhus/awesome-observables/readme"}},"next":{"id":"cbb6ce44-1e3f-5628-82a1-b3dd9861e24d","fields":{"repo":"Richienb/awesome-ponyfills","slug":"/Richienb/awesome-ponyfills/readme"}}},"pageContext":{"repo":"RyanZim/awesome-npm-scripts","id":"b0cb11a9-e97f-59f9-b0bc-1b168aa082e8","previousId":"6517901e-70a1-59f6-aaee-ef1d70da31c7","nextId":"cbb6ce44-1e3f-5628-82a1-b3dd9861e24d"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}